subSubSection.paragraph:
Description (amended from
Komai & Tachikawa, 2008
). Carapace 0.24 of total body length; rostrum spiniform, directed slightly downward, falling slightly short of or nearly reaching midlength of eyestalk, anterolateral projection obtuse; anterolateral concavity moderately deep, with tiny cleft; dorsal oval well defined, smooth, cervical groove across about posterior 0.2 of carapace length; linea thalassinica extending to posterolateral margin of carapace.
